DataElement.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Thyroxine Outcome Lower Limit of Normal Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the lowest value of the range of statistical characteristics that are supposed to represent accepted standard, non-pathological pattern related to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for thyroxine, the major hormone derived from the thyroid gland and is peripherally deiodinated to form TRIIODOTHYRONINE which exerts a broad spectrum of stimulatory effects on cell metabolism

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for thyroxine, the major hormone derived from the thyroid gland and is peripherally deiodinated to form TRIIODOTHYRONINE which exerts a broad spectrum of stimulatory effects on cell metabolism.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: A procedure for critical evaluation; a means of determining the presence, quality, or truth of something.

Concepts.definition: Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample of blood, urine, or other body substance in a laboratory setting.

Property.preferredDefinition: The major hormone derived from the thyroid gland. Thyroxine is synthesized via the iodination of tyrosines (MONOIODOTYROSINE) and the coupling of iodotyrosines (DIIODOTYROSINE) in the THYROGLOBULIN. Thyroxine is released from thyroglobulin by proteolysis and secreted into the blood. Thyroxine is peripherally deiodinated to form TRIIODOTHYRONINE which exerts a broad spectrum of stimulatory effects on cell metabolism.:Outcome; a phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

Concepts.definition: A hormone synthesized and secreted by the thyroid gland containing four iodine atoms and is converted to triiodothyronine (T3) in the body, influencing metabolism and organ function.

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: the value, units of measure not specified, of the lowest value of the range of statistical characteristics that represent accepted standard, non-pathological patterns, for a particular laboratory result or other quantitative parameter.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: The bottom of the normal range for a particular laboratory result.:The information contained in a data field.
